For those interested in editing the ppmck wiki, go to its main page and click the silly button &quot;Join&quot; at the top, just over the red warning. The password is &quot;ppmck on FAMICOM&quot;, without the quotes but with the caps, they are necessary. You'll need a wikidot account, which you can create after joining.<br /><br />Also, it's a great thing that ppmck is on GitHub. It seems that one of the latest additions is detection of overload―I suppose it detects when the engine takes more that one frame to run…<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=336">Jarhmander</a> — Sat Jul 27, 2013 1:44 pm</p><hr />
