<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10320&amp;p=115724#p115724"><![CDATA[
You're going to be a bit constrained with using the envelope channel for pitches; the sunsoft 5b runs at (effectively) ≈½ the speed of e.g. the ZX Spectrum or Atari ST's sound.<br />In practice, you'll have something like the bottom octave or so of well-tuned notes.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Sat Jul 27, 2013 2:18 am</p><hr />
